author: dblevins
msg: Reverting that last commit. Looks like we have the choice between a split package or a circular dependency.  Not sure which is better from an OSGi standpoint.

Only potential way I can see to clean it all up is to split the javax.enterprise.inject.spi and javax.enterprise.context.spi packages into a new geronimo-jcdi-spi_1.0_spec module, though I'm not sure that will work either as they are both subpackages of javax.enterprise.inject.* and javax.enterprise.context.* respectively.

author: jvanzyl
msg: MECLIPSE-632: This is part of partitioning user behavior for Maven support in Eclipse. No more halfway, if you want to use M2Eclipse then you import your projects using M2Eclipse. If you want to use "mvn eclipse:eclipse" then this structure will not be supported in M2Eclipse 1.0 and there shouldn't be any confusion to users. The M2Eclipse developers will no longer support this behavior because it's getting out of control at this point.
